
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Prereq: Cloonix must be installed in your host machine.
To create om iso a cloonix-capable VM:

Go into confvars and:
Modify NAME, TYPE, LANG, ISO and BULK in confvars to suit your needs.

TYPE can be only: buster stretch, opensuse, ubuntu,
                  centos8 redhat8 fedora30.
LANG can be only: us, fr.

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1)
call ./iso_install.sh and proceed with the installation as usual.
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2)
./run.sh optionnaly, for the welcome and setting of the root password to root.

On some distributions, you have to run the VM a first time to finish the
installation, on some, the password for root is not configured, for the redhat,
you have to accept the licence before start. For all these cases, call the
./run.sh script and do the necessary, the password for root must be root for the
next step that is done with ./backdoor_install.sh.
Note that you may choose another root password, but in that case, before
launching ./backdoor_install.sh, you must put this password in the C code 
file src/oper_auto.c (where "root" is written twice)and call ./cmd to build.
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3)
call ./backdoor_install.sh and wait for shutdown.
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------

For the VM available on clownix.net site user "cloonix", password "cloonix" and
user "root" password "root".
